Certainly! Developing a smart card application with C++ can be done using the GlobalPlatform specification, which is a standard for managing applications on secure chip technology, including smart cards.

To get started with developing a smart card application using C++, you will need to:

1. Obtain a smart card reader and a smart card development kit that supports C++ development.
2. Install the development environment for the smart card, which typically includes a compiler, linker, and other tools needed to develop and test the smart card application.
3. Create a new project in the development environment and specify the target platform as the smart card you are developing for.
4. Write the smart card application code using C++ and the GlobalPlatform specification. This will typically involve defining the data structures and functions needed for your application and using the GlobalPlatform API to interact with the smart card.
5. Compile and link the smart card application code into a binary file that can be loaded onto the smart card.
6. Test the smart card application using a smart card reader and a testing tool that supports C++ development.

Here is an example of how to develop a smart card application using C++:
```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <gp/gp.h>

int main()
{
    gp_context_t ctx;
    gp_init(&ctx);

    gp_device_t device;
    gp_connect_device(&ctx, "OMNIKEY CardMan 5321", &device);

    gp_card_t card;
    gp_connect_card(&ctx, &device, &card);

    gp_channel_t channel;
    gp_open_channel(&ctx, &card, 0x01, &channel);

    // Send APDU commands to the smart card
    unsigned char apdu[] = {0x00, 0xA4, 0x04, 0x00, 0x08, 0xA0, 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x03, 0x10, 0x00, 0x00};
    unsigned char response[256];
    size_t response_len = sizeof(response);
    gp_transmit_apdu(&ctx, &channel, apdu, sizeof(apdu), response, &response_len);

    gp_close_channel(&ctx, &channel);
    gp_disconnect_card(&ctx, &card);
    gp_disconnect_device(&ctx, &device);
    gp_finish(&ctx);

    return 0;
}
```
This example code uses the GlobalPlatform API to connect to a smart card reader, connect to a smart card, open a channel, send APDU commands to the smart card, and close the channel and disconnect from the smart card. Note that the exact code needed for your specific smart card application will depend on the requirements of your project and the specific smart card being used.
